<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>If you plan to switch from the old ntfs-3g to the new ntfs3 included in the kernel, be warned that all symlinks on the partition created with ntfs-3g will be unrecognized by ntfs3, forcing you to recreate them (breaking stuff like WINE prefixes or other programs relying on them)</p> <p>You can just move all symlinks to another drive before changing and all will work fine when you move them back</p> <p>EDIT: wrong driver name</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/ClangPan"> /u/ClangPan </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w6tq6k/small_psa_for_people_switching_from_ntfs3g_fuse/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w6tq6k/small_psa_for_people_switching_from_ntfs3g_fuse/">[comments]</a></span>